# Quality Gates

## Pre-Implementation Gate

Before writing code for a feature, verify:

- [ ] Requirements and acceptance criteria are clear and complete.
- [ ] Architecture decisions are documented.
- [ ] Data model and API contracts are defined.
- [ ] Dependencies and blockers are identified.
- [ ] The feature can be implemented as a vertical slice.

## Per-Feature Gate

After implementing each feature, validate:

### Functionality
- [ ] All acceptance criteria are met (happy path + error paths).
- [ ] Edge cases are handled (empty, null, boundary values, concurrent access).
- [ ] Error messages are user-friendly and actionable.
- [ ] Loading, empty, and error states are implemented in UI.

### Code Quality
- [ ] Code follows all applicable global and tech-specific rules.
- [ ] No linter errors or warnings.
- [ ] No hardcoded values that should be configurable.
- [ ] No `TODO` or `FIXME` left without a tracking ticket.
- [ ] Dead code is removed. No commented-out blocks.

### Testing
- [ ] Unit tests cover business logic and edge cases.
- [ ] Integration tests verify component interactions.
- [ ] Tests are deterministic and isolated.
- [ ] Test names describe behavior, not implementation.
- [ ] Code coverage meets project threshold (aim for 80%+ on business logic).

### Security
- [ ] User input is validated and sanitized.
- [ ] Authentication and authorization are enforced.
- [ ] No secrets in code or configuration files.
- [ ] SQL injection, XSS, CSRF protections in place.
- [ ] Sensitive data is encrypted at rest and in transit.

### Performance
- [ ] No N+1 queries. Database queries are optimized.
- [ ] API responses are paginated for list endpoints.
- [ ] Assets are optimized (images, bundles, lazy loading).
- [ ] No memory leaks (cleanup in effects, unsubscribe, close connections).

### Accessibility (UI)
- [ ] Semantic HTML is used correctly.
- [ ] Interactive elements are keyboard-navigable.
- [ ] Color contrast meets WCAG AA (4.5:1 minimum).
- [ ] Screen reader labels are present on all interactive elements.
- [ ] Focus management is correct for modals and dynamic content.

## Pre-Release Gate

Before deploying to production:

- [ ] All feature gates pass.
- [ ] E2E tests pass on critical user flows.
- [ ] Performance benchmarks are within acceptable bounds.
- [ ] Security audit checklist is complete.
- [ ] Documentation is up to date (README, API docs, changelog).
- [ ] Environment variables and secrets are configured for production.
- [ ] Rollback plan is documented and tested.
- [ ] Monitoring and alerting are configured.

## Continuous Quality

- Run linter and formatter on every commit (pre-commit hooks).
- Run unit tests on every push (CI pipeline).
- Run integration tests on every PR.
- Run E2E tests before every deployment.
- Review dependency vulnerabilities weekly.
